CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 3, 1962, pg. 10A reads: "Kappa Silhouettes - Eleven of the 15 members of the Kappa Alpha Psi Silhouettes pose for this picture, which was taken at their 12th annual "Black and White Ball" at the Hilton Hotel, last Friday night. Seated (left to right): Mmes. Helen Smith, chairman; Ethel Walden, Helen Hailstock and Ethel Stewart.  Standing: Mmes. Alma Davis, Nancy Pitts, co-chairman; Harriet Thomas, Ann Barnett, Ruth Greenlee, Louise Ford, president, and Frances Turner. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of seven members of the Kappa Alpha Psi Silhouettes, left to right: Alma Davis, Nancy Pitts, Francis Turner, Ann Barnett, Helen Smith, Ethel Stewart, and Louise Ford, gathered in Hilton Hotel for Black and White Ball
